WEBVTT

00:00:00.638 --> 00:00:02.850
To all captains, lieutenants,

00:00:02.975 --> 00:00:05.352
and squad members of all ranks
within the Seireitei!

00:00:06.185 --> 00:00:08.103
<i>Substitute Soul Reaper
Ichigo Kurosaki</i>

00:00:08.105 --> 00:00:09.772
<i>is heading to the Soul Society!</i>

00:00:11.483 --> 00:00:14.277
His Bankai cannot be stolen
by the Quincies!

00:00:14.777 --> 00:00:15.778
What?!

00:00:16.946 --> 00:00:17.905
Ichigo is...

00:00:17.907 --> 00:00:19.866
He's on his way, huh?!

00:00:20.116 --> 00:00:21.118
Ichigo...

00:00:21.784 --> 00:00:22.786
Ichigo...!

00:00:23.286 --> 00:00:24.579
Akon, huh?

00:00:25.079 --> 00:00:27.707
How dare he act on his own.

00:00:30.418 --> 00:00:32.295
Once Ichigo Kurosaki joins us,

00:00:32.295 --> 00:00:33.795
the tide of battle
will turn in our...

00:00:33.796 --> 00:00:36.216
– Wait.
– What is it, Third Seat Akon?

00:00:37.341 --> 00:00:38.343
Something's wrong.

00:00:38.719 --> 00:00:41.679
Ichigo Kurosaki's
Spiritual Pressure in the Garganta...

00:00:42.680 --> 00:00:43.682
It disappeared.

00:00:43.807 --> 00:00:46.893
{\an8}"DISCONNECTED"

00:00:47.143 --> 00:00:48.353
Look into it right away.

00:00:48.728 --> 00:00:50.438
And also send
the Secret Remote Unit

00:00:50.438 --> 00:00:51.606
to the Senkaimon exit!

00:00:51.856 --> 00:00:52.858
Yes, sir!

00:00:57.445 --> 00:00:58.447
Jidanbo?!

00:00:58.739 --> 00:01:00.573
What the hell are you doing?!

00:01:10.209 --> 00:01:12.293
Damn it...
What the hell is this?!

00:01:17.049 --> 00:01:19.676
{\an8}"AKON"

00:01:20.177 --> 00:01:22.763
Sorry! I don't know how,
but I got trapped...

00:01:28.227 --> 00:01:30.436
What's going on?!
What's happening, Akon?!

00:01:30.813 --> 00:01:32.188
– Akon!
– <i>Evacuate!</i>

00:01:32.188 --> 00:01:34.856
– <i>Hiyosu!</i>
– <i>You too, Akon! Get going!</i>

00:01:34.858 --> 00:01:38.736
{\an8}"AKON"

00:01:39.153 --> 00:01:41.030
– <i>Damn it. All I can hear are</i>
– Rukia!

00:01:41.031 --> 00:01:42.448
– <i>screams and explosions!</i>
– Renji!

00:01:42.908 --> 00:01:46.409
<i>Help... Somebody help us!
Help!</i>

00:01:46.411 --> 00:01:48.703
– <i>I'm going to kill you, bastards!</i>
– <i>No! I can't take this anymore!</i>

00:01:48.704 --> 00:01:50.873
<i>You call yourselves members of
the 13 Court Guard Squads?!</i>

00:01:50.998 --> 00:01:55.002
<i>It hurts... It hurts!</i>

00:01:57.548 --> 00:01:58.549
Don't give up...!

00:01:58.674 --> 00:01:59.925
We must stand our ground!

00:02:00.758 --> 00:02:04.471
Ichigo will come... I know he will!

00:02:32.039 --> 00:02:36.752
{\an8}<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:02:36.919 --> 00:02:41.967
{\an8}<i>At my wit's end, I feel
a growing frustration</i>

00:02:42.425 --> 00:02:46.805
{\an8}<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:02:47.139 --> 00:02:50.558
{\an8}<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:02:51.018 --> 00:02:56.981
{\an8}<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:02:57.274 --> 00:03:00.193
{\an8}<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:03:01.402 --> 00:03:06.407
{\an8}<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:03:06.699 --> 00:03:09.286
{\an8}<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:03:09.453 --> 00:03:13.955
{\an8}<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:03:13.956 --> 00:03:16.752
{\an8}<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:03:16.919 --> 00:03:21.756
{\an8}<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:03:21.757 --> 00:03:24.300
{\an8}<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:03:24.425 --> 00:03:26.301
{\an8}<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:03:26.302 --> 00:03:30.014
{\an8}<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:03:30.306 --> 00:03:33.977
{\an8}<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:03:34.144 --> 00:03:37.062
{\an8}<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:03:37.063 --> 00:03:41.776
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:03:55.915 --> 00:03:59.669
It seems he's on a rampage inside.

00:03:59.877 --> 00:04:01.754
But it's no use...

00:04:02.338 --> 00:04:05.216
His Majesty granted me
the letter "J"!

00:04:05.384 --> 00:04:07.677
Quilge Opie, "The Jail"!

00:04:07.677 --> 00:04:11.807
There's no way you can escape
from that prison!

00:04:13.809 --> 00:04:14.810
Now then...

00:04:15.101 --> 00:04:19.189
Before the power that I absorbed
from that monster disappears...

00:04:19.898 --> 00:04:22.858
I should eliminate
all of you as well...

00:04:25.237 --> 00:04:26.196
No!

00:04:33.452 --> 00:04:35.413
<i>Who could have done that?!</i>

00:04:37.415 --> 00:04:38.416
<i>Shit...!</i>

00:04:45.048 --> 00:04:46.048
Damn it...

00:04:46.550 --> 00:04:47.675
Even with Getsuga...

00:04:48.468 --> 00:04:51.887
I can't break this thing
even with Getsugatensho?!

00:04:55.725 --> 00:04:56.976
– Captain!
– Stay back!

00:04:58.312 --> 00:05:00.480
Watch me fight...

00:05:01.230 --> 00:05:03.190
and figure out his abilities!

00:05:03.858 --> 00:05:06.569
I-If that's the plan,
then let me go first!

00:05:06.862 --> 00:05:09.697
Since my Senbonzakura
has been stolen,

00:05:09.697 --> 00:05:12.783
your Bankai is our last hope...

00:05:13.367 --> 00:05:14.411
Captain...

00:05:14.786 --> 00:05:17.456
I'm going to draw out
his abilities.

00:05:18.122 --> 00:05:20.166
I want you to stay there
and watch for now...

00:05:23.586 --> 00:05:27.466
<i>Why does it feel like
my limbs are freezing?</i>

00:05:28.716 --> 00:05:32.928
<i>Are those thorns of light
covered with some kind of poison?!</i>

00:05:34.096 --> 00:05:35.932
I see you've noticed...

00:05:36.350 --> 00:05:38.894
You're wondering if it's poison,
aren't you?

00:05:40.269 --> 00:05:41.437
It's not.

00:05:42.271 --> 00:05:48.235
This is something that you lost
a long time ago.

00:05:48.569 --> 00:05:50.654
Retrace your memories.

00:05:51.281 --> 00:05:52.783
You became a captain...

00:05:52.949 --> 00:05:54.408
You became strong...

00:05:54.826 --> 00:05:57.954
You became able to
overpower your enemies...

00:05:58.288 --> 00:06:01.665
It's a sensation you haven't felt
in a long time, isn't it?

00:06:02.375 --> 00:06:08.173
That is the most important
sensation for a person to survive.

00:06:10.216 --> 00:06:11.675
It is called "fear."

00:06:14.346 --> 00:06:16.973
Fear? The Captain?

00:06:17.766 --> 00:06:20.309
For those who have been
struck by my arrows,

00:06:20.310 --> 00:06:22.978
all sorts of things turn into fear.

00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:28.317
"What if I reach for my sword,
or if I draw it?"

00:06:28.610 --> 00:06:31.862
"What if I swing it up,
or swing it down?"

00:06:32.197 --> 00:06:36.367
"What if I move my fingers,
or shift my gaze?"

00:06:36.492 --> 00:06:39.329
"What if I breathe in,
or breathe out?"

00:06:39.704 --> 00:06:43.165
"Maybe something fatal will occur."

00:06:43.750 --> 00:06:47.086
Anything and everything
is suspicious,

00:06:47.086 --> 00:06:50.339
making it impossible
to even think straight.

00:06:52.259 --> 00:06:57.721
But you are enduring it so far
by sheer force of will.

00:06:58.055 --> 00:06:59.473
You are a threat.

00:07:00.057 --> 00:07:02.810
But that's all it is.
A threat.

00:07:03.269 --> 00:07:05.855
It can hardly compare to "fear."

00:07:06.355 --> 00:07:09.358
The core of your soul is already...

00:07:11.653 --> 00:07:14.738
consumed by your fear of me.

00:07:15.699 --> 00:07:16.867
<i>Ridiculous.</i>

00:07:17.367 --> 00:07:20.036
<i>There is no battle without fear.</i>

00:07:21.454 --> 00:07:26.375
<i>I have accepted and overcome
my fear of battle.</i>

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.670
<i>I gained the strength
to move forward.</i>

00:07:30.172 --> 00:07:31.338
<i>I have nothing to fear—</i>

00:07:38.180 --> 00:07:41.266
"Fear can be conquered
with experience."

00:07:42.141 --> 00:07:43.892
The stronger and
more experienced you are,

00:07:43.894 --> 00:07:45.853
the harder you fall
for that illusion.

00:07:47.355 --> 00:07:49.899
Fear that has a cause is easy.

00:07:50.817 --> 00:07:52.235
If there is a cause to it,

00:07:52.735 --> 00:07:54.904
then by removing that cause,

00:07:55.112 --> 00:07:57.908
you also remove
what you think is fear.

00:07:59.074 --> 00:08:02.995
But true fear has no cause.

00:08:03.997 --> 00:08:07.666
That's because it's not an emotion.
It is instinct.

00:08:08.375 --> 00:08:10.295
True fear...

00:08:10.836 --> 00:08:13.839
has no cause or limits.

00:08:13.964 --> 00:08:16.634
It crawls up your body

00:08:17.134 --> 00:08:20.764
like countless flies.

00:08:21.181 --> 00:08:25.809
We cannot... escape our instincts.

00:08:35.153 --> 00:08:36.153
What?!

00:08:58.467 --> 00:08:59.469
Brother?

00:09:13.274 --> 00:09:15.485
There is nothing you can do.

00:09:15.860 --> 00:09:20.990
You cannot defeat your own Bankai
with just your Shikai.

00:09:21.865 --> 00:09:26.580
Senbonzakura... doesn't belong to
a bastard like you!

00:09:29.624 --> 00:09:30.667
Brother!

00:09:31.167 --> 00:09:34.211
Are you turning your back toward
the enemy during battle?

00:09:34.712 --> 00:09:36.755
I feel insulted.

00:09:45.974 --> 00:09:46.975
Zabimaru!

00:10:10.456 --> 00:10:11.582
Stop it...

00:10:15.294 --> 00:10:17.504
Stop it!

00:10:17.630 --> 00:10:18.673
Ban...

00:10:28.307 --> 00:10:29.308
You fool.

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:32.354
He was about to use his Bankai.

00:10:32.645 --> 00:10:34.813
You could have stolen it.

00:10:35.148 --> 00:10:39.318
What?!
I thought only captains had Bankai!

00:10:39.860 --> 00:10:43.907
You need to go back and reread
His Majesty's Daten.

00:10:56.669 --> 00:10:57.671
<i>Renji...</i>

00:10:59.547 --> 00:11:00.548
<i>Rukia...</i>

00:11:08.847 --> 00:11:09.849
<i>Forgive me.</i>

00:11:27.783 --> 00:11:30.787
{\an8}THE SEIREITEI – NEAR SHORYU GATE

00:11:42.090 --> 00:11:43.091
Hey.

00:11:43.674 --> 00:11:46.720
Are you the boss of these losers?

00:11:48.011 --> 00:11:49.221
Kenpachi Zaraki!

00:11:52.225 --> 00:11:54.226
Three Stern Ritters dead?

00:11:55.102 --> 00:11:57.438
{\an8}STERN RITTER "Q" "THE QUESTION" /
"R" "THE ROAR" / "Y" "THE YOURSELF"

00:11:58.273 --> 00:11:59.732
But how...?!

00:12:00.482 --> 00:12:02.277
There's not much to explain.

00:12:02.860 --> 00:12:05.654
The first one, the big guy,
was trash.

00:12:06.530 --> 00:12:09.366
He attacked me
by turning into a giant monkey

00:12:09.491 --> 00:12:11.660
that could blast his enemies
with just his voice.

00:12:13.455 --> 00:12:15.331
So I split him in two.

00:12:16.039 --> 00:12:18.000
– <i>"The Question"! I object to everything</i>
– The second one

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:20.085
– <i>about you, Kenpachi Zaraki!</i>
– got on my nerves talking about

00:12:20.086 --> 00:12:22.254
– <i>Anyone that I object to will be—</i>
– objecting to everything about me.

00:12:22.922 --> 00:12:25.091
So I tore out his throat.

00:12:25.633 --> 00:12:27.802
The third guy wasn't too bad.

00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:30.764
He transformed into me, after all.

00:12:32.389 --> 00:12:35.601
I struggled a bit
because I was fighting myself.

00:12:37.604 --> 00:12:42.357
But that just meant I had to become
stronger than his impression of me.

00:12:43.817 --> 00:12:45.986
I heard you were a monster...

00:12:46.738 --> 00:12:47.572
but now I understand.

00:12:47.572 --> 00:12:50.741
I've got no business with
a scrawny pale guy like you.

00:12:54.037 --> 00:12:55.663
I came here...

00:12:56.371 --> 00:12:59.042
to fight <i>you</i>!

00:12:59.292 --> 00:13:00.293
Your Majesty!

00:13:11.929 --> 00:13:17.058
{\an8}"GENJI-JUKU"

00:13:17.059 --> 00:13:18.061
Rukia...

00:13:22.731 --> 00:13:23.691
Damn it...!

00:13:23.982 --> 00:13:24.984
Damn it!

00:13:29.572 --> 00:13:30.822
Break!

00:13:30.823 --> 00:13:32.366
Break, damn it!

00:13:35.620 --> 00:13:36.703
I won't let you die...

00:13:37.705 --> 00:13:39.666
I won't let <i>any</i> of you die...!

00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:42.585
I'm going to...

00:13:43.711 --> 00:13:46.464
I <i>will</i> protect you all!

00:13:47.256 --> 00:13:52.677
{\an8}GARGANTA – SEIREITEI SIDE APERTURE

00:13:52.678 --> 00:13:53.428
– Y-Yes, sir!
– Y-Yes, sir!

00:13:55.431 --> 00:13:57.767
{\an8}FRONT OF SQUAD 9 BARRACKS

00:14:01.562 --> 00:14:02.562
It sucks!

00:14:02.563 --> 00:14:06.317
It sucks, it sucks,
it sucks, it sucks!

00:14:06.609 --> 00:14:10.279
It sucks to be so weak,
doesn't it, Lieutenant?!

00:14:10.488 --> 00:14:12.490
{\an8}STERN RITTER "O" "THE OVERKILL"

00:14:12.782 --> 00:14:15.618
<i>Damn it!
I'm no match for him...</i>

00:14:16.034 --> 00:14:18.620
Are you scared of my strength?

00:14:19.371 --> 00:14:22.375
His Majesty granted me
the letter "O"!

00:14:22.875 --> 00:14:24.793
"The Overkill."

00:14:25.086 --> 00:14:27.589
Whether it be
friend or foe or beast,

00:14:27.714 --> 00:14:30.549
the more I kill,
the stronger I get!

00:14:31.341 --> 00:14:33.719
I've already killed
a hundred people

00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:34.721
since I got here today.

00:14:36.556 --> 00:14:38.640
The last time I came,
it was also a hundred.

00:14:38.807 --> 00:14:42.312
I remember killing a lieutenant
just like you!

00:14:47.317 --> 00:14:48.525
So it was you...!

00:14:49.652 --> 00:14:51.613
I did it...

00:14:51.821 --> 00:14:52.822
like this!

00:14:58.827 --> 00:14:59.828
H...

00:15:00.913 --> 00:15:02.331
Head Captain!

00:15:08.129 --> 00:15:10.380
This is my lucky day!

00:15:10.631 --> 00:15:11.591
Head Captain!

00:15:11.591 --> 00:15:14.092
I came here for you!

00:15:14.635 --> 00:15:16.596
I'm going to use
your subordinate's Bankai...

00:15:17.054 --> 00:15:20.265
...to end your life!

00:15:20.975 --> 00:15:22.351
Bankai...

00:15:24.394 --> 00:15:26.147
{\an8}BANKAI

00:15:28.357 --> 00:15:31.068
{\an8}KOKO GONRYO RIKYU

00:15:37.991 --> 00:15:39.701
Doesn't this bring back memories?!

00:15:39.869 --> 00:15:44.289
I heard this guy hadn't used
this Bankai in over 2,000 years!

00:15:44.539 --> 00:15:47.210
You get to see it once more!

00:15:47.543 --> 00:15:49.711
You should be thanking me!

00:15:50.587 --> 00:15:53.256
<i>So this is
Lieutenant Sasakibe's Bankai?!</i>

00:15:54.216 --> 00:15:56.759
<i>I had no idea there was
a Zanpakuto aside from Hyorinmaru...</i>

00:15:56.760 --> 00:15:58.346
<i>that could control the weather!</i>

00:16:05.852 --> 00:16:07.855
Master Eijisai...

00:16:08.230 --> 00:16:09.731
Master Eijisai Yamamoto!

00:16:11.567 --> 00:16:18.950
{\an8}FOUNDER OF GENRYU STYLE / GENJI-JUKU
GRAND MASTER SHIGEKUNI YAMAMOTO

00:16:19.450 --> 00:16:21.702
Hey!
Don't call me Eijisai!

00:16:22.035 --> 00:16:23.578
F-Forgive me, sir!

00:16:24.330 --> 00:16:27.624
<i>For some reason, each time
I distinguished myself in battle,</i>

00:16:27.625 --> 00:16:30.628
<i>the name Eijisai
became more widely used.</i>

00:16:31.129 --> 00:16:33.505
<i>I didn't care much for that.</i>

00:16:34.673 --> 00:16:37.801
But, Master Eijisai,
I cannot be so audacious

00:16:37.802 --> 00:16:40.053
as to call you by your real name!

00:16:40.679 --> 00:16:42.639
What is with you, anyway?!

00:16:42.764 --> 00:16:44.725
You're not even one of my students,

00:16:44.725 --> 00:16:46.644
and yet,
you hang around here every day!

00:16:47.352 --> 00:16:50.314
I come here hoping to be
your right-hand man!

00:16:50.731 --> 00:16:53.233
In that case, all the more reason
for you to become my student!

00:16:53.734 --> 00:16:55.611
If you rise to the rank of master,

00:16:55.737 --> 00:16:57.488
you'll naturally become
my right-hand man!

00:16:57.989 --> 00:16:59.614
No, Master Eijisai,
if I become your student,

00:16:59.615 --> 00:17:01.784
then I will only be mimicking you.

00:17:02.285 --> 00:17:04.494
A right-hand man must be one
who can compensate

00:17:04.619 --> 00:17:06.413
for the things you are
unable to handle!

00:17:07.039 --> 00:17:08.665
You're always splitting hairs...

00:17:08.790 --> 00:17:11.461
Also, I haven't shown up every day.

00:17:12.002 --> 00:17:13.671
This is my first time here
in a month.

00:17:14.881 --> 00:17:16.715
As you told me to a month ago,

00:17:17.799 --> 00:17:19.760
I have acquired a Bankai.

00:17:20.094 --> 00:17:21.095
Oh?

00:17:21.721 --> 00:17:26.308
In that case, try to defeat me
with that Bankai of yours.

00:17:27.018 --> 00:17:29.979
{\an8}RUKON DISTRICT –
EAST 37 DISTRICT, RYUGON

00:17:33.857 --> 00:17:34.858
Bankai!

00:17:35.276 --> 00:17:36.943
Koko Gonryo Rikyu!

00:17:54.628 --> 00:17:56.713
<i>It was a magnificent Bankai.</i>

00:17:57.256 --> 00:18:00.050
<i>He wasn't able to defeat me, but...</i>

00:18:00.468 --> 00:18:05.681
<i>His Bankai left a permanent scar
on my forehead.</i>

00:18:06.973 --> 00:18:08.934
That Bankai is like a newborn.

00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:11.436
That's right.

00:18:12.188 --> 00:18:15.566
I intend to spend the rest of
my life honing this Bankai

00:18:15.691 --> 00:18:18.568
so it can be helpful to you,
Master Eijisai!

00:18:19.737 --> 00:18:22.323
<i>His words contained no lies.</i>

00:18:22.824 --> 00:18:25.910
<i>After years of grueling training,</i>

00:18:26.618 --> 00:18:31.582
<i>everybody in the Soul Society
came to know Chojiro's name.</i>

00:18:32.959 --> 00:18:36.670
<i>When my scar dried, it looked like
the Japanese character "Ju,"</i>

00:18:36.671 --> 00:18:40.173
<i>so everyone started
calling me Jujisai.</i>

00:18:41.424 --> 00:18:44.260
I cannot allow the scar I gave you

00:18:44.261 --> 00:18:46.847
to be a reason to change your name,
Master Eijisai.

00:18:47.640 --> 00:18:49.558
<i>Everyone except Chojiro...</i>

00:18:49.683 --> 00:18:52.686
<i>He stubbornly continued to
call me Eijisai.</i>

00:19:00.278 --> 00:19:01.570
{\an8}"RYU (WILLOW)"

00:19:01.778 --> 00:19:03.865
<i>So for Chojiro's sake,</i>

00:19:04.323 --> 00:19:07.491
<i>I took on the name Genryusai.</i>

00:19:07.492 --> 00:19:09.202
{\an8}"GENRYUSAI"

00:19:11.580 --> 00:19:13.082
Head Captain!

00:19:13.415 --> 00:19:15.667
Hey!
What's the matter, old man?!

00:19:15.835 --> 00:19:17.669
Have you lost the strength
to even retaliate

00:19:17.670 --> 00:19:19.963
after getting hit by
your subordinate's Bankai?!

00:19:20.463 --> 00:19:22.842
Come on, say something!

00:19:29.472 --> 00:19:31.017
Chojiro...

00:19:31.726 --> 00:19:33.560
I can feel your frustration...

00:19:34.604 --> 00:19:38.941
I understand your anger... very well...

00:19:40.151 --> 00:19:44.571
Because I know...
the Bankai that you had honed...

00:19:45.780 --> 00:19:48.241
is absolutely not this weak!

00:19:52.663 --> 00:19:53.788
<i>Burn...</i>

00:19:55.124 --> 00:19:59.795
<i>I'm finally able to give you
a proper send-off.</i>

00:20:02.088 --> 00:20:03.548
<i>Chojiro...</i>

00:20:04.799 --> 00:20:06.509
<i>Farewell.</i>

00:20:12.599 --> 00:20:13.601
Do not worry.

00:20:14.101 --> 00:20:16.729
Every last member
of the rebel army...

00:20:17.939 --> 00:20:20.650
I will slaughter them
with my own hand.

00:20:27.990 --> 00:20:29.616
The Head Captain...

00:20:30.660 --> 00:20:32.953
The Head Captain is furious!

00:20:34.204 --> 00:20:38.208
I've... never felt the Head Captain
get this angry before...

00:20:38.209 --> 00:20:40.795
You idiot.
Neither have I.

00:20:41.836 --> 00:20:45.215
That includes him
fighting on the front lines.

00:20:46.549 --> 00:20:48.970
Look at how hard
the Head Captain is fighting.

00:20:49.636 --> 00:20:53.641
We captains and lieutenants
can't let ourselves be defeated.

00:20:53.974 --> 00:20:54.976
You're right, sir.

00:21:03.692 --> 00:21:04.693
Get up!

00:21:05.027 --> 00:21:07.487
We cannot let ourselves
lie on the ground

00:21:07.488 --> 00:21:09.323
while Master Genryusai
still stands!

00:21:09.573 --> 00:21:11.199
As a Court Guard Squad member,

00:21:11.200 --> 00:21:13.411
that would be
an unacceptable disgrace!

00:21:15.578 --> 00:21:16.663
– Sir!
– Yes, sir!

00:21:18.039 --> 00:21:19.625
Whoa, wait a minute...

00:21:20.209 --> 00:21:22.711
You guys were as good as dead
a second ago...

00:21:22.711 --> 00:21:24.505
What's going on here?

00:21:25.381 --> 00:21:27.424
This is a real problem, isn't it?

00:21:28.800 --> 00:21:30.301
Old Man Yama's Spiritual Pressure

00:21:30.303 --> 00:21:32.471
is reverberating throughout
the Seireitei.

00:21:33.638 --> 00:21:35.266
It's giving me goosebumps.

00:21:35.682 --> 00:21:37.684
Like he's scolding me...

00:21:38.560 --> 00:21:41.563
As if he's saying, "I don't remember
raising you to be a coward..."

00:21:41.564 --> 00:21:44.567
"Who'd struggle against
an enemy of this level!"

00:21:53.241 --> 00:21:56.244
{\an8}<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:21:56.412 --> 00:22:00.623
{\an8}<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:00.624 --> 00:22:05.046
{\an8}<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:05.171 --> 00:22:09.383
{\an8}<i>We lie buried as we glare
into the distance</i>

00:22:09.759 --> 00:22:12.385
{\an8}<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:12.510 --> 00:22:15.637
{\an8}<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:15.638 --> 00:22:18.099
{\an8}<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:18.224 --> 00:22:20.101
{\an8}<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:20.102 --> 00:22:21.185
{\an8}<i>Touching</i>

00:22:21.186 --> 00:22:24.606
{\an8}<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:22:24.773 --> 00:22:28.026
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:22:28.027 --> 00:22:34.282
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:22:34.657 --> 00:22:38.287
{\an8}<i>It cannot be undone
and cannot be stopped</i>

00:22:38.453 --> 00:22:41.624
{\an8}<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:22:41.832 --> 00:22:46.545
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:22:46.670 --> 00:22:48.713
{\an8}<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:22:48.923 --> 00:22:50.214
{\an8}<i>Take everything</i>

00:22:50.215 --> 00:22:54.970
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:22:55.096 --> 00:22:57.012
{\an8}<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:22:57.013 --> 00:22:58.891
{\an8}<i>Along with our world</i>

00:22:59.933 --> 00:23:03.228
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:03.229 --> 00:23:09.652
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now
visible to us</i>

00:23:09.777 --> 00:23:13.655
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:13.823 --> 00:23:17.159
{\an8}<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:23:18.618 --> 00:23:22.664
One of the Special Threats,
Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:23:24.666 --> 00:23:27.001
Is this the best you can do?

00:23:28.503 --> 00:23:29.587
How frail.

00:23:30.713 --> 00:23:35.469
It seems I've overestimated
you people.

00:23:36.261 --> 00:23:37.262
Go to sleep.

00:23:40.307 --> 00:23:43.769
It's been a thousand years,
hasn't it, Yhwach?

00:23:44.936 --> 00:23:48.982
I've come to put an end
to your life.

00:23:56.281 --> 00:23:58.616
<i>"The heart burns."</i>

00:23:59.617 --> 00:24:01.619
<i>"Even though the rain falls."</i>

